parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause metal fragments to pass through the airbag material, resulting in serious injury or death to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: as the issue is related to a recall and potential failure

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair for Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave vehicle occupants at risk of serious injury or death, and can also affect the value and usability of the vehicle.
symptoms: Inability to use the front passenger seat
and uncertainty about when the repair will be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat back panel adhesion can cause the seat back to become loose or detached, potentially leading to injuries or distractions while driving, and compromising the safety of passengers in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat back panel is loose or detached
the panel is separating from the seat
the mechanisms of the heated seats are exposed
the seat back is leaning on passengers while driving
the velcro adhesive is not working
the connectors at the top of the seat back are missing or not installed correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sudden and catastrophic failure of the steering rack can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The front wheels and steering wheel freeze
making it impossible to steer the vehicle
